  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2527382627" />
    <a title="Donna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13244359-donna"><img alt="Donna" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1396758075p2/13244359.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2527382627?book_show_action=true">Sep 29, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Donna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Donna" href="/user/show/13244359-donna">Donna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2527382627" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10100337941085767862">I didn&apos;t know this was one of &quot;those&quot; romance books. Really....it&apos;s on the bottom of my genre preferences. <br/><br/>I liked Laney, the MC. I thought the author portrayed her with enough details to create interest and likability. Nick as a character however, was like a male diva. He seemed like so much work. I don&apos;t care how good looking he was...I need more than that. Ugh. <br/><br/>Besides Nick, I didn&apos;t care for the writing. It was predictable, repetitive, and some of this was just painful from dialogue to descr</span>
  <span id="freeText10100337941085767862" style="display:none">I didn't know this was one of "those" romance books. Really....it's on the bottom of my genre preferences. <br /><br />I liked Laney, the MC. I thought the author portrayed her with enough details to create interest and likability. Nick as a character however, was like a male diva. He seemed like so much work. I don't care how good looking he was...I need more than that. Ugh. <br /><br />Besides Nick, I didn't care for the writing. It was predictable, repetitive, and some of this was just painful from dialogue to descriptive strokes. Now even with that said, some of the descriptive strokes were creatively written, but they were not the norm here. So 2 stars. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10100337941085767862" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


